==Description==

The '''Mesh HarmonizeNormals''' command harmonizes the normals of mesh objects.

==Usage==

# Select one or more mesh objects.
# There are several ways to invoke the command:
#* Press the {{Button|[[Image:Mesh_HarmonizeNormals.svg|16px]] [[Mesh_HarmonizeNormals|Harmonize Normals]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|Meshes → [[Image:Mesh_HarmonizeNormals.svg|16px]] Harmonize Normals}} option from the menu.

==Notes==

* This command can produce a mesh with flipped normals. The [[Mesh_FlipNormals|Mesh FlipNormals]] command can be used to correct this.
* For a clear indication of the orientation of the faces of mesh objects make sure the {{PropertyView|Lighting}} property of the mesh objects is set to {{Value|One side}}. The color of the back side of their faces will then depend on the backlight settings: {{MenuCommand|Edit → Preferences → Display → Light Sources → Backlight}}. See: [[Preferences_Editor#Light_Sources|Preferences Editor]].


